org.franca.core.franca

Interface FQualifiedElementRef

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, FExpression, FInitializerExpression, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FQualifiedElementRefImpl

    public interface FQualifiedElementRef
extends FExpression
    A representation of the model object 'FQualified Element Ref'. TODO: update This class is a reference to some ref:FrancaModelAPIReference_FTypedElement[FTypedElement]. If the referenced element is no compound type (i.e., struct or union), only the e[element] property will be used. The e[target] and e[field] properties will be null. If a field of a compound type is referenced, the e[field] property will point to the ref:FrancaModelAPIReference_FField[FField] object. If the compound type is nested, the e[target] property will reference the next outer level (which is itself a compound referenced by a ref:FrancaModelAPIReference_FTypedElementRef[FTypedElementRef]. This might be chained in order to specify a reference to a deeply nested compound element.

    The following features are supported:

    • Element
    • Qualifier
    • Field
